article id=570 dt=Text ctime=3922998217 mtime=3923000028 nm=utf8.reformat
#_result = utf8.reformat (pattern, ...)
#_
#_**Parameters:**
#_  pattern : string
#_  ...     : 0 or more additional arguments
#_
#_**Returns:**
#_  result  : string
#_
#_**Description:**
#_  This function is similar to utf8.format except for char '{' which must
#_  be written as '%{'.
#_  
#_  {1}, {2}, etc. in the pattern are substituted by values corresponding
#_  to parameters' numbers in the '%s' format.
#_
#_  If the number in curly braces is followed by a ':' then this part becomes
#_  a "%" in the format string. E.g. {3:04d} is replaced by value of the 3-rd
#_  parameter in the '%04d' format.
#_
#_**Note:**
#_  This is an added function, not present in the original luautf8 library.
#_
#_**Example:**
#_  reformat('Wrong count: {3:10} {1} {3} and {2:.4f}. Ok: %{ %06d %s and %s }',
#_           111, 222, 'three')
#_

